content:
Session records store information about agents' and customers' interactions online, such as chat requests processed, time spent online, or active engagement in chats. Make the Chat sessions tab visible to users assigned to specified permission sets.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud.

To set tab visibility for Chat features: Manage Profiles and Permission Sets.

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. Migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date to avoid service interruptions.

Alternatively, give users access to the Chat sessions tab through profiles.
title: Setting Chat Sessions Tab Visibility in Service Cloud
